     ffoolldd - fold long lines for finite width output device

SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
     ffoolldd [--ww _w_i_d_t_h] _f_i_l_e _._._.

DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
     FFoolldd is a filter which folds the contents of the specified files, or the
     standard input if no files are specified, breaking the lines to have max-
     imum of 80 characters.

     The options are as follows:

     --ww      Specifies a line width to use instead of the default 80 charac-
             ters.  _W_i_d_t_h should be a multiple of 8 if tabs are present, or
             the tabs should be expanded using expand(1) before using ffoolldd.

SSEEEE AALLSSOO
     expand(1)

BBUUGGSS
     If underlining is present it may be messed up by folding.

